mycourtjester wrote:

&gt;I am interested in using the Heritrix extractors to pull links from 
&gt;HTML documents.  The problem is that in addition to the links, I 
&gt;need to know the position in the document that the links occur.  
&gt;This should be possible with the regex Matcher, but it does not look 
&gt;like it is currently supported in the code.  Am I missing 
&gt;something?  Would this be a useful use case for anyone else?
&gt;  
&gt;
Its not currently supported.

To know the position of each link in a page, you&#39;ll need to doctor each 
of the extractors you&#39;re interested in to log the link found and its 
offset. You might want to run the links found through UURIFactory; it&#39;ll 
test for wholesomeness; might save you logging too many trash URIs. 

Related, crawl.log gives a primitive picture showing the page a link 
came out of.

I&#39;m sure others would be interested in such a facility if you were to 
develop it.  Perhaps start by posting a patch to the list.

